Israeli rave goers run for their lives when Hamas paraglide in and start shooting
description: The sun had just risen over Israelâ€™s Negev desert, and at the all-night outdoor rave at Kibbutz Reâ€™im, the party was still going. Thumping trance music was playing full volume, and under brightly-coloured canopies, hundreds of revellers were dancing themselves into exhaustion. #Israel #Gaza #Hamas Then, just as chill-out time began to beckon, uninvited guests arrived. On footage captured by a partygoerâ€™s mobile phone, several small black dots can be seen approaching in the dawn sky from the direction of Gaza. As the cameraman shouts what appears to be a warning, fellow revellers ignore him, unable to hear because of the music.  Moments later, the dancing stops as the airborne arrivals are revealed as motorised paragliders carrying armed Hamas militants. As rocket fire also begins, the dancers flee for their lives â€“ chased by gunmen bent on shooting or kidnapping anyone in their path.  Following the rampage, which began at around 7am on Saturday, dozens of partygoers were reported to have been killed or kidnapped, with many more still missing. The unconscious body of a dreadlocked female attendee was later paraded through Gaza in a truck, as passers-by spat on her. Among those reported to have been captured was a 26-year-old British citizen, Jake Marlowe, who was helping with security at the rave. title: What we know about the Hamas attack on an Israeli music festival
description: The Hamas attack on the Tribe of Nova music festival is the worst civilian massacre in Israel.  Hamas militants opened fire on about 3,500 young Israelis who had come together for the Jewish holiday of Sukkot. At least 260 festival-goers were killed. #shorts #Israel #Hamas

title: Detik-detik Hamas Serang Festival Musik di Israel
description: Dilaporkan anak-anak muda yang menghadiri festival musik Tribe of Nova Trance di dekat Kibbutz Re'im di Israel selatan diserang oleh Hamas pada hari Sabtu (7/10/2023). Pasukan Hamas sebelumnya berhasil menerobos pagar penjaga Israel yang dijaga ketat dan masuk ke wilayah itu dari Gaza dan meluncurkan serangan ke festival musik itu.  Jumlah korban tewas hingga Senin (9/10/2023) tercatat sebanyak 260 orang. Tak hanya itu, dilaporkan masih ada beberapa warga yang dinyatakan hilang.  Simak selengkapnya dalam video berikut!  Penulis Naskah: Vina Muthi Ambarwati Narator: Vina Muthi Ambarwati Video Editor: Vanness Grace Lee Produser: Firzha Ananda Putri  Musik: Hopeless - Jimena Contreras  #SeranganHamasdiFestivalMusikIsrael #Hamas #Israel #Palenstina #Gaza #JernihkanHarapan  Artikel ini bisa dilihat di : https://video.kompas.com/watch/943248/detik-detik-hamas-serang-festival-musik-di-israel

title: How Hamas fighters broke into a kibbutz (Oct 7 2023)
description: CCTV shows how two Hamas fighters broke into a kibbutz community.  The two fighters tried to crawl under the gate and when that failed, they hid in the security booth.   Shortly after a resident's vehicle arrived at the gate and the pair ambushed the driver, killing all the passengers. title: Thousands attend London rally calling on Hamas to release hostages
description: A pro-Israel demonstration took place in London as part of calls for the safe return of hostages from Gaza.  Protesters in Trafalgar Square are held up photos of those missing, with their names being read out from the steps of the National Gallery.  Security in the square was high with a significant police presence. title: Ceasefire protesters interrupt Senate hearing
description: Protesters calling for a ceasefire in Gaza disrupted a Senate Committee hearing about a funding request for Israel and Ukraine, with testimony from Secretaries Blinken and Austin. More than 25 protesters were escorted out of the hearing room. Some in the group were quietly holding up their hands painted in red. Others were shouting "ceasefire now" exiting the room, and some left quietly with their hands up with red dye. title: Israel Shows Thermobaric Grenades Hamas Used In October 7 Attack
description: The Israeli army displayed on November 1 a large cache of weapons and supplies obtained from Hamas militants following the attack on October 7.  The weapons seized included Hamas' RPGs, thermobaric grenades, rockets and other weaponry.  Israeli tanks have been active inside Gaza for at least four days following weeks of air bombardments in retaliation for an attack by Palestinian Hamas militants on mostly Israeli civilians on Oct. 7 and the taking of more than 200 hostages.  #israel #gaza #hamas   n18oc_world      n18oc_crux  CRUX is your daily video news guide to the big events that are shaping our world. title: Norm Finkelstein on Jewish Protests For Ceasefire
description: Watch the full conversation with Norm and Dan here: https://youtube.com/live/33KsfEWs9Mw  Norman Finkelstein on his reaction to the Ceasefire protests in NYC.  Norman Finkelstein is a political scientist, prolific author, and son of Holocaust survivors. He received his PhD from the Princeton University Politics Department in 1987. He is the author of many books that have been translated into 60 foreign editions, including THE HOLOCAUST INDUSTRY: Reflections on the exploitation of Jewish suffering, and GAZA: An inquest into its martyrdom, I'LL BURN THAT BRIDGE WHEN I GET TO IT! Heretical Thoughts on Identity Politics, Cancel Culture, and Academic Freedom. In the year 2020, Norman Finkelstein was named the fifth most influential political scientist in the world.   Dan Kovalik is a labor and human rights lawyer living in Pittsburgh.  He taught International Human Rights at the University of Pittsburgh School of Law from 2012 to 2023.  He is the author of several books, including "Cancel This Book: The Progressive Case Against Cancel Culture" https://a.co/d/86FTTHP  ***Please support The Katie Halper Show *** For bonus content, exclusive interviews, to support independent media & to help make this program possible, please join us on Patreon - https://www.patreon.com/thekatiehalpershow  Get your Katie Halper Show Merch here! https://katiehalper.myspreadshop.com/all  Follow Katie on Twitter: @kthalps

title: Israeli forces have killed over 10,000 Palestinians in Gaza since October 7
description: The death toll in Gaza has now surpassed 10,000, as Israeli strikes continue to pound the war-torn and besieged territory almost one month into the war.  According to the latest figures published by the Gaza health ministry today, Israeli strikes have killed at least 10,022 Palestinians - of which 4,104 were children - since Israel's brutal onslaught on the Gaza Strip began on 7 October.  Hundreds - if not thousands - more are also feared to be still trapped under rubble.  After Israeli forces carried out intense bombardment on Sunday night/early Monday alone, the Gaza health ministry said more than 200 people were killed.  Many witnesses and journalists described Israel's indiscriminate bombardment overnight as the "heaviest experienced so far" on social media, amid yet another communications blackout.  ğŸ¥: @alexander.durie   #gaza #gazastrip #gazaunderattack #gaza_under_attack #gazasiege #freepalestine #palestine #israel

title: Moment Hamas militants take civilian hostage in Israel
description: Newly released footage shows Hamas militants attacking and restraining Israeli civilians just outside Kissufim kibbutz as attacks unfolded across the region on October 7. title: Rally in Jerusalem calls for release of Israeli hostages held in Gaza
description: (7 Nov 2023)  FOR CLEAN VERSION SEE STORY NUMBER: 4462285  ASSOCIATED PRESS Jerusalem - 6 November 2023 ++DAY SHOTS++ 1. Various of protest outside Parliament HEADLINE: Rally in Jerusalem calls for release of hostages ANNOTATION: Family members and supporters of the hostages held by Hamas protested outside Israelâ€™s parliament in Jerusalem to call for their release. 2. SOUNDBITE (English) Sarah Cytryn, protester: â€œWe want to know that theyâ€™re alive. We want their families to know that they are not alone. I think for all of us, the ultimate goal is to get them back and to have them free.â€ 3. Various of protest ANNOTATION: More than 240 hostages were taken from Israel into Gaza during an unprecedented incursion by Hamas in southern Israel on Oct. 7. 4. SOUNDBITE (English) Ellen Geffen, protester: â€œWe have to win this war, we have to achieve a sense of security, we have to rebuild our homes â€“ but nothing will be worth it if we donâ€™t bring them back.â€ ++NIGHT SHOTS++ 5. Various of images of hostages projected on a wall  ANNOTATION: As an act of support, images of the hostages were projected on the walls of Jerusalemâ€™s old city. ANNOTATION: The Hamas surprise attack has led to a war that has now killed more than 1,400 people in Israel and over 10,000 in Gaza. STORYLINE: Hundreds of family members and supporters of the hostages held by Hamas protested outside Israelâ€™s parliament in Jerusalem to call for their release.  More than 240 hostages were taken from Israel into Gaza during an unprecedented incursion by Hamas in southern Israel on Oct. 7.  As an act of support, images of the hostages were also projected on the walls of Jerusalemâ€™s old city.  The Hamas surprise attack has led to a war that has now killed more than 1,400 people in Israel and over 10,000 in Gaza.   AP video shot by Sam McNeil and Moshe Edri   ===========================================================  Clients are reminded to adhere to all listed restrictions and to check the terms of their licence agreements. title: October 7 Israeli Helicopter Friendly-fire reports
description: An investigation into the 7 October Hamas attack on Israel found that an Israeli army helicopter, that arrived on the scene of the music festival that was targeted, was responsible for at least some of the deaths of Israelis, as the helicopter shot festival goers as well as Hamas operatives, Israel's Haaretz newspaper reported on Saturday.  Investigators said that the target for Hamas' attack seemed to be a Kibbutz, but changed plans once the festival was discovered.  Israeli Police have reportedly since issued a statement reacting and denouncing the Haaretz report that an IDF helicopter that arrived at the site of the Supernova festival near Reâ€™im on October 7 may have killed some Israeli civilians.  Hamasâ€™ spokesman in Beirut, Osama Hamdan, announced on Sunday that the Israeli military helicopter likely killed some Israeli festival goers. Adding that Hamasâ€™ fighters did not have weapons capable of causing the damage that burnt cars and bodies at the festival. title: Over 1,500 interfaith protesters shut down Manhattan Bridge to call for ceasefire
description: More than 1,500 interfaith protesters shut down the Manhattan Bridge in New York for hours on Sunday, the busiest travel day of the year, demanding a permanent ceasefire in Gaza.  The demonstration was the latest ceasefire protest by Jewish Voice for Peace, which previously staged sit-ins at US Congress, Grand Central Terminal and the Statue of Liberty. title: Israelis Rally In Tel Aviv Calling For Immediate Release Of Remaining Hostages In Gaza
description: Israelis rallied in Tel Aviv on December 2 night, calling for the immediate release of the remaining captives in Gaza.  A seven-day truce, during which Hamas had released more than 100 hostages, collapsed on December 1, halting any further hostage releases in exchange for Palestinian prisoners held in Israeli jails.  Michael Levy, the brother of 33-year-old hostage Or Levy, said he joined the rally to show "we are not backing down" on the demand for their loved ones to be freed.  The family of 70-year-old Luis Har said they were experiencing a "nightmare" waiting for the grandfather to be returned home.  More than 240 people - Israelis and foreign nationals - were abducted to Gaza on Oct 7. by Hamas militants who burst through the border with Israel and killed 1,200 people, according to local authorities.  Israel, vowing to wipe out Hamas, responded with a bombing campaign and ground offensive that has destroyed large areas of Gaza and killed more than 15,000 people, according to the health ministry in the Hamas-run enclave.  #israel #hamas #gaza #protest #ceasefire #worldnews   n18oc_world      n18oc_crux  CRUX is your daily video news guide to the big events that are shaping our world. title: â€œNow, Nowâ€ | Freed Hostages Want Israel To Make A Deal With Hamas To Free Gaza Captives
description: In Tel Aviv, thousands demanded urgent action from the Israeli government to secure the release of hostages held by Hamas in Gaza. The rally followed the tragic incident where three hostages were mistakenly shot by Israeli forces. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu hinted at renewed negotiations, emphasizing the pressure exerted by Israel's recent offensive in Gaza. Former captives, Maya Regev and Danielle Aloni, urged for a new swap deal, as over 100 hostages remain in Gaza, prompting calls for international intervention, including Red Cross access. title: Israeli Woman Released By Hamas, Calls For Talks To Free More Hostages
description: A woman who had been held hostage by Hamas and released in late November, called for renewed negotiations to free more people being held captive in Gaza at a rally on Saturday. Raz Ben-Ami was among those taken hostage during an October 7 attack by Hamas on southern Israel, and was released on November 29. title: Israelis protest outside American embassy in Jerusalem calling for ceasefire
description: About a hundred men and women staged a protest outside the US embassy in Jerusalem, coming together to mourn the casualties in Gaza. The gathering called for a ceasefire and an end to the ongoing cycle of bloodshed. The demonstration featured a recorded message from a Palestinian refugee and a clip from a Gaza music producer killed in the Israeli air strikes. Families in Tel Aviv hold rally for release of hostages held in Gaza
description: Family members of hostages held in Gaza held a rally in Tel Aviv, demanding their release.  An attack led by Hamas on Israel on 7 October resulted in the deaths of over 1,200 people.  Around 240 people were taken back to Gaza as captives during the attack. More than 100 of them were released in a prisoner swap deal last month, but some 130 remain held in Gaza. title: Families of Gaza hostages continue rally for release
description: (8 Jan 2024)   FOR CLEAN VERSION SEE STORY NUMBER: 4471622  RESTRICTION SUMMARY: ASSOCIATED PRESS Tel Aviv, Israel - 07 January 2024 1. Various of shoes on Tel Avivâ€™s promenade, people walking and running by HEADLINE: Families of Gaza hostages continue rally for release ANNOTATION: A line of shoes was displayed on Tel Avivâ€™s promenade as families of the hostages held in Gaza rallied to call for the release of their relatives.  ANNOTATION: The display was organizedÂ three monthsÂ after Hamas militants stormed southern Israel, killing 1,200 people andÂ taking 250 people hostage.  2. Various of people laying down shoes 3. Close of shoes ANNOTATION: A number of hostages had been released during a short Israel-Hamas ceasefire in November but over 100 still remain in Gaza.  4. Osnat Sharabi laying shoes 5. Close of shoes ANNOTATION: The display was initiated by Osnat Sharabi, whose brothers are among the hostages still held captive by Hamas.   6. SOUNDBITE (English) Osnat Sharabi, sister ofÂ Gaza hostages: â€œI felt that the public is forgetting the hostages. I felt the government and the world stopped doing any actions to bring them home. And I have this very, distressing feeling.â€  7. Various of shoes on display ANNOTATION: Israel said it will continue the war that has now killed nearly 23,000 Palestinians in Gaza until Hamas is eliminated and noÂ longerÂ a threat. STORYLINE: A line of shoes was displayed on Tel Avivâ€™s promenade as families of the hostages held in Gaza rallied to call for the release of their relatives.   The display was organizedÂ three monthsÂ after Hamas militants stormed southern Israel, killing 1,200 people andÂ taking 250 people hostage.  A number of hostages had been released during a short Israel-Hamas ceasefire in November but over 100 still remain in Gaza.  The display was initiated by Osnat Sharabi, whose brothers are among the hostages still held captive by Hamas.   â€œI felt that the public is forgetting the hostages. I felt the government and the world stopped doing any actions to bring them home,â€ Sharabi said.   Israel said it will continue the war that has now killed nearly 23,000 Palestinians in Gaza until Hamas is eliminated and noÂ longerÂ a threat.  AP Video shot by Ami Bentov  ===========================================================  Clients are reminded to adhere to all listed restrictions and to check the terms of their licence agreements. title: Former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi accuses Gaza ceasefire protesters of having ties with Russia
description: In a recent interview on CNN's "State of the Union," former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi suggested that some of the protesters in the US demanding a ceasefire in Gaza could be connected to Russia.   She expressed her belief that while some of these protesters are spontaneous, organic, and sincere, others might be linked to Russian President Vladimir Putin. Pelosi also pointed out that the call for a ceasefire aligned with what Putin would like to see, paralleling the situation in Ukraine.   Without providing concrete evidence, she called on the FBI to investigate the potential Russian financing of these protests.  Pelosi's comments have been the subject of criticism. However, her comments are also notable as they mark the first time a prominent US lawmaker has accused Russia's leader of backing protesters calling for a ceasefire in Gaza.  #gaza #gaza_strip #palestine #freepalestine #congress #putin #ceasefirenow #russia #nancypelosi

title: Fetterman Calls Out Ceasefire Protesters For Not Demanding Hamas Surrender

title: Judith Butler: "October 7 was an act of armed resistance"
description: â€œI think it is more honest and historically correct to say that the uprising of October 7 was an act of armed resistance."  Judith Butler, a prominent theorist and member of Jewish Voice for Peace, framed Hamasâ€™s attack on southern Israel as an act of armed resistance, but she advocated for room for debate around the manner in which it conducted the attacks. title: Protests for Gaza erupt across Arab world
description: Large protests in solidarity with Gaza erupted in major Arab cities over the weekend, including Amman, Baghdad, Cairo, Tangier and Casablanca.   Protesters chanted songs in solidarity with Palestinian resistance and against normalisation with Israel, as well as calling for an immediate ceasefire in Gaza.   In Amman, where many people are of Palestinian descent, over 2,000 demonstrators gathered and clashed with riot police officers as they tried to march towards the Israeli embassy in protest.   Meanwhile, in Egypt, where the right to protest has been severely restricted by the state, protesters gathered at the Press Syndicate in Cairo and condemned the government's complicity in the escalating humanitarian crisis in Gaza.  #ceasefirenow #gaza #palestine #protests

title: Protests Across Israel As Hostage Families Call For Parliament Rally | Dawn News English
description: Thousands congregated outside the Israeli parliament in Jerusalem, staging the largest anti-government rally since the onset of Israel's offensive in Gaza. Demonstrators demanded government intervention for a ceasefire and the release of Israeli captives held by Hamas.   The protest follows a record-breaking gathering in Tel Aviv. Participants assert that the rally marked the most significant demonstration since the conflict's inception.   Criticism has mounted against Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's administration for security lapses during the Hamas-led attack on southern Israel, resulting in numerous casualties and hostages. Palestinian authorities report a death toll exceeding 32,000, predominantly comprising women and children.  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Dawn News English is your window into the latest news, insight, and features from South Asia and beyond. title: Massive Israeli rally demanding ceasefire deal and hostage release
description: Nearly 50,000 Israelis took to the streets in West Jerusalem on Sunday, urging their government to sign a ceasefire deal for the release of hostages held in Gaza.  Sunday also marks the six-month duration since the Israel-Hamas conflict broke out on Oct 7, 2023. The protesters expressed hope that Israeli hostages will be brought back home early and safely and that Gaza people will resume normal life. title: Thousands rally for Gaza hostages in Jerusalem | AFP
description: Thousands gather in front of Israel's parliament in Jerusalem to demand the return of the hostages in Gaza abducted by Hamas militants six months ago. Although truce talks on ending the bloodiest war in Gaza between Israel and Palestinian militants have resumed, Israel has repeatedly ruled out a ceasefire without the return of the hostages taken by Hamas in its 7 October attack. title: British journalist corrects framing of Israeli war at Columbia University
description: British journalist Mona Chalabi corrected the framing of the Israel-Gaza war to the Israel-Palestine war when she received a Pulitzer Prize at Columbia University. In solidarity with the students of New York University facing suspension and arrest for supporting Palestine, she posted a video recorded in October 2023. In her brief speech, Chalabi emphasised the reluctance of many attending the ceremony to address the Palestine issue. She noted that although she wasn't scheduled to give a speech, she found it necessary due to factual inaccuracies. The British data journalist, illustrator, and writer of Iraqi descent received the prize for Illustrated Reporting and Commentary from Columbia University President Emeritus Lee Bollinger last October. On 19 April 2024, she mentioned that she had emailed the President of Columbia in March but had not received a response. In sharing the video, Chalabi extended her support to student protesters at Columbia University in New York, who organised the Gaza Solidarity Encampment. Over 100 pro-Palestinian protesters were arrested following its organisation. Several students at Columbia University have also been suspended from the university and its affiliated institutions. It's noteworthy that Chalabi won the Prize for her striking illustrations, which blend statistical reporting with insightful analysis. These illustrations provide readers with a deeper understanding of Amazon founder Jeff Bezos's vast wealth and economic influence. title: Relatives of Israeli hostages rally outside prime minister's office calling for cease-fire deal
description: (3 Jun 2024)   FOR CLEAN VERSION SEE STORY NUMBER: 4497976  RESTRICTION SUMMARY: ASSOCIATED PRESS Jerusalem - 2 June 2024 1. Protesters calling for a deal to release hostages following U.S. President Joe Biden announcement on aÂ proposed agreementÂ  2. Pan of protest  3. Protester holding banner reading (Hebrew) â€œa deal now or we are all in vainâ€ 4. Pan of protest  5. SOUNDBITE  (English) Shay Dickmann, cousin of Israeli hostageÂ Carmel Gat: â€œIâ€™m here to support my government in taking this deal, the deal that Netanyahu suggested, our prime minister, that will get all our people (hostages) back home. We are all here in support for the return of all hostages.â€ 6. Dickmann speaking at protest  7. SOUNDBITE (English) Shay Dickmann, cousin of Israeli hostageÂ Carmel Gat: ++PARTIALLY OVERLAID WITH SHOT 9++ â€œIâ€™m optimistic. I feel like this is the chance for me to see my cousin, and for 125 families to reunite and for the state of Israel to feel whole again when our people are back home.â€ 9. Various of protest  STORYLINE: Relatives of hostages held in Gaza gathered near the Israeli Prime Minister's office in Jerusalem on Sunday, calling on Benjamin Netanyahu and his War Cabinet to accept the proposed agreement announced by U.S. President Joe Biden to end the fighting in Gaza.   Among them was Shay Dickmann, cousin of Israeli hostageÂ Carmel Gat.   She said she was "optimistic" and that the deal would present a chance for "Israel to feel whole again when our people are back home.â€  Netanyahu called a permanent cease-fire in Gaza a â€œnonstarterâ€ until long-standing conditions for endingÂ the warÂ are met, appearing to undermine the proposal that Biden described as an Israeli one.   Mediators the U.S., Egypt and Qatar pressed Israel and Hamas, saying the proposed deal â€œoffers a road map for a permanent cease-fire and ending the crisisâ€ and gives immediate relief to both hostages and Gaza residents.   Biden on Friday asserted that Hamas militants are â€œno longer capableâ€ of carrying out a large-scale attack on Israel like the one on Oct. 7.   He urged Israel and Hamas to reach an agreement to release about 100Â remaining hostages,Â along with the bodies of around 30 more, for an extended cease-fire.  AP video shot by Ami Bentov  ===========================================================  Clients are reminded to adhere to all listed restrictions and to check the terms of their licence agreements. title: Several Thousand Rally In Tel Aviv Demanding Hostage Release | Subscribe to Firstpost
description: Several Thousand Rally In Tel Aviv Demanding Hostage Release | Subscribe to Firstpost  Tens of thousands of protesters rallied in Tel Aviv on June 22, calling for the release of hostages held by Hamas in Gaza and an immediate ceasefire to the war. Such protests have become weekly events since the October 7th attack by Hamas. The protest saw scuffles as Israeli police attempted to disperse the crowd near the ruling Likud party headquarters.  ---  Tel Aviv | Hostage | Protest | Hamas | Gaza | Likud Party | Israel | Attack | Ceasefire | Police | Headquarters | Firstpost | News Live | World News | Latest News | Global News | International News | News | Trending News  #telaviv #hostage #protest #hamas #gaza #likudparty #israel #attack #ceasefire #police #headquarters #firstpost #newslive #worldnews #latestnews #globalnews #news #internationalnews #trendingnews  Firstpost is an Indian news and media website. title: Israeli forces used Hannibal Protocol against Israelis on October 7
description: A new report reveals that Israeli forces employed the Hannibal protocol on October 7, risking the lives of their own captives to prevent the capturing of Israeli soldiers.   Haaretz highlighted failures in Israeli military intelligence, showing many Israelis were exposed to Israeli fire during the operation. title: Israeli defence minister blames himself, Netanyahu and the cabinet for Oct 7 failures
description: Yoav Gallant, Israel's defence minister, calls for his nation's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to be investigated for the security failures on Oct 7, alongside himself and other members of the cabinet.   He addressed a military officers' graduation ceremony and delivered these remarks with the PM present. title: Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu addresses Congress about Oct. 7 attack
description: "Proportionately ... that's like 20 9/11's in one day."  Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu addressed Congress amid Israel's ongoing war with Hamas, underscoring that Oct. 7th "is a day that will forever live in infamy" and compared Hamas' attack on Israel to Sept. 11, 2001 for America.

title: Year Later, Israeli Survivors Reflect On The Lingering Toll Of October 7 Attack
description: A year after the Oct. 7 attack by Hamas on Israel, the anniversary of the assault has hit survivors particularly hard. With the Israel-Hamas war raging on, survivors reflect on the day a year ago that changed their lives forever.  They hid in bedrooms, bomb shelters, safe rooms and beneath trees as Hamas militants poured across the border.  In the aftermath, they've mourned loved ones, struggled with anxiety, suffered survivor's guilt and questioned whether they will ever return home to places that still bear the scars of their ordeal.  #israel #israelhamaswar #indiatoday #itwebvideos      Subscribe to India Today for NEW VIDEOS EVERY DAY and make sure to enable Push Notifications so you'll never miss a new video. title: Pro-Palestinian rallies staged worldwide ahead of October 7 anniversary
description: Thousands of people rallied around the world Saturday in support of Palestinians in Gaza ahead of the one-year anniversary of the October 7 Hamas attack, in which around 1,200 people were killed and 250 others taken hostage.  The subsequent war Israel launched against Hamas in Gaza has killed more than 41,000 Palestinians, according to the health ministry there. #cnn #news #gaza #protests

title: October 7 survivor speaks at Sydney Jewish vigil | ABC News
description: Michal Ohana was at the Nova Music Festival on October 7 2023 when it was attacked by Hamas. She says speaking at a Jewish vigil in Sydney remembering the attack is a way to speak for those who didn't survive. title: Anniversary Of October 7 Attack On Israel | 10 News First
description: On October 7, 2023, Hamas militants launched rockets and staged a ground attack on Israel, marking the start of a bloody conflict in the Middle East. title: How October 7 Shook Israeli Society
description: Before: The 2010s was, largely speaking, a prosperous and peaceful decade for Israel. The country witnessed economic growth propelled by the high-tech sector. Meanwhile, with the Second Intifada having subsided and the construction of the West Bank security barrier, the Israeli-Palestinian conflict largely faded from view for the average Israeli. 2019 began a series of crises that disrupted the sense of normalcy: Prime Minister Netanyahuâ€™s criminal indictments, four elections in the span of three years, COVID-19, Netanyahuâ€™s defeat and return thanks to the support of the far-right, and the judicial overhaul. A handful of hot-button issues plagued Israeli society and occupied Israelisâ€™ concerns prior to October 7, including religion-and-state controversies, the rising cost of living, and security concerns amid a rise in terrorism. But by and large they enjoyed a quality of life and standard of living comparable to Western nations.  After: October 7 violated Israelisâ€™ sense of security in their own country, undermining a core promise of the state to keep Jews safe. It shattered Israelisâ€™ trust in their government and security establishment. For the first time in years, the conflict with the Palestinians and with the Iranian axis at large was not a distant idea, but lethal attacks experienced directly and indirectly by all Israeli society. Hamas murdered nearly 1,200 innocent people in their homes and at an outdoor raveâ€”places that embodied safety and community. With 101 hostages still in Gaza, tens of thousands still displaced from the north, and soldiers still fighting on the front, October 7 is not an event of the past, but an ongoing reality that has left Israeli society in a constant state of trauma and precarity. Both politically and in terms of security, the path forward out of the morass is far from certain.

title: A look at Gaza City before and after October 7 ahead of 1st anniversary of Hamas attacks
description: (6 Oct 2024)  FOR CLEAN VERSION SEE STORY NUMBER: 4523593  ASSOCIATED PRESS Gaza City, Gaza Strip - 23 March 2021 1. Various of drone shots showing Omar Al-Mukhtar street in Gaza City before the war   ASSOCIATED PRESS Gaza City, Gaza Strip -  18 September 2024 2. Various of destruction in Omar Al-Mukhtar street   ASSOCIATED PRESS Gaza City, Gaza Strip - 23 March 2021 3. Drone shot of traffic movement on Al-Mukhtar Street in Gaza City  ASSOCIATED PRESS Gaza City, Gaza Strip -  18 September 2024 4. Traveling shots of destruction in Gaza city building   ASSOCIATED PRESS Gaza City, Gaza Strip - 18 June 2022 5. Drone shots showing Gaza City before the war   ASSOCIATED PRESS Gaza City, Gaza Strip -  19 September 2024 6. Various of destruction in Gaza City   ASSOCIATED PRESS Gaza City, Gaza Strip - 18 June 2022 7. Drone shots showing Gaza city before the war   ASSOCIATED PRESS Gaza City, Gaza Strip -  19 September 2024 8. Travelling shot showing destroyed building in Gaza City  STORYLINE: A year of fighting between Israel and Palestinian militants has left the Gaza Strip in ruins, levelling entire neighbourhoods and destroying large swaths of farms across the Palestinian enclave.  Gaza City, the power seat of Hamasâ€™s rule for the past 16 years, has arguably seen most of the destitution, especially the cityâ€™s eastern and southern neighbourhoods.  The area around the Shifa hospital, Gazaâ€™s largest medical facility which the Israeli military raided twice, was flattened to the ground, Associated Press drone footage before and after the war showed.  The seaside areas, including the Shatie refugee camp, have also experienced massive destruction, the footage showed.  High-rise buildings overlooking the Mediterranean Sea have turned into rubble, and the seaside thoroughfare - one of the two south-north highways in the Strip - is marked by rubble and destroyed buildings on its sides.  Israelâ€™s military assault on Gaza, triggered by Hamasâ€™ attacks in southern Israel on Oct. 7, has stretched for one year, with recent escalation between Israel and Hezbollah and Iran threatens to engulf the entire Middle East.  The Gaza war has killed about 42,000 Palestinians, according to Gazaâ€™s Health Ministry. The ministry, part of Gazaâ€™s Hamas government, does not differentiate between fighters and civilians in its count though it says about half of the dead have been women and children. Israel says at least 17,000 militants are among the dead.  The war has caused vast destruction and displaced around 90% of Gazaâ€™s population of 2.3 million people, often multiple times.  U.N. Secretary-General AntÃ³nio Guterres told The Associated Press last month that the war has caused the worst death and destruction he has seen in his more than seven-year tenure.  AP video by Wafaa Shurafa  ===========================================================  Clients are reminded to adhere to all listed restrictions and to check the terms of their licence agreements. title: Protesters block major highway in Tel Aviv at weekly rally for hostages still held in Gaza
description: (13 Oct 2024)   FOR CLEAN VERSION SEE STORY NUMBER: 4525408  RESTRICTION SUMMARY: ++NIGHT SHOTS++ ASSOCIATED PRESS  Tel Aviv, Israel - 12 October 2024 1. Various of protesters with banners, flags and portraits of Israeli hostages 2. Sign reading (English) "Hostage deal now" 3. SOUNDBITE (English) Naama Weinberg, protest organiser: â€œI expect that our government and our prime minister have took this Yom Kippur (Jewish holiday) and really looked deep in and admitted to himself, and I hope that this would go out to the press, that there were times that there was a deal on the table and he could have took it and he could have released the hostages. And we know that also now there is a deal on the table. It could be possible. And the only thing that is making it not happen is Netanyahu's personal interest and his beliefs.â€ 4. Various of protests  5. Various of woman holding up flare  STORYLINE: Hundreds of Israeli protesters blocked one of the main boulevards in central Tel Aviv on Saturday as part of a weekly demonstration to demand a deal to return the remaining hostages held in Gaza.  Saturday's demonstration came a day after hundreds gathered in Tel Aviv's Hostages Square on Yom Kippur, the holiest day in the Jewish calendar, when Jews atone and repent for sins committed in the previous year.  Naama Weinberg, one of the organisers of the protest, said she hoped that Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu took the holy day to question his actions.   "There is a deal on the table. It could be possible. And the only thing that is making it not happen is Netanyahu's personal interest," she told the Associated Press.   It's been a full year since Hamas-led militants blew holes in Israelâ€™s security fence and stormed into army bases and farming communities, killing some 1,200 people, mostly civilians, and abducting another 250.   They are still holding about 100 captives inside Gaza, a third of whom are believed to be dead.  Meanwhile, Israelâ€™s retaliatory offensive in Gaza has killed over 42,000 Palestinians, according to local health authorities, who do not say how many were fighters but say women and children make up more than half of the fatalities.   The war has destroyed large areas of Gaza and displaced about 90% of its population of 2.3 million people, often multiple times.  In the last month Israel has also stepped up its campaign against Hezbollah with waves of heavy airstrikes across Lebanon and a ground invasion at the border.  Lebanese authorities said said Friday that 60 people were killed and 168 wounded in the past 24 hours, raising the total toll over the past year of conflict between Israel and the Hezbollah to 2,229 dead and 10,380 wounded.   AP video by Nicolae Dumitrache  ===========================================================  Clients are reminded to adhere to all listed restrictions and to check the terms of their licence agreements. title: Central Park Rally | Voices for Israel Hostages Amidst Tensions
description: Central Park Rally | Voices for Israel Hostages Amidst Tensions  Description Witness the powerful rally in Central Park where pictures of hostages were displayed as attendees prayed and sang for their safe return. This Sunday event is part of a series of demonstrations marking the one-year anniversary of the ongoing conflict, featuring both pro-Israel and pro-Palestinian groups. The NYPD is on high alert, increasing patrols to ensure safety and prevent radicalization among attendees. Join us to explore the sentiments shared during this poignant gathering and the broader implications for peace and safety in our communities. title: Israeli activists protest against Gaza, Lebanon war outside the defence ministry in Tel Aviv
description: "It's just spreading murder, killing, and disaster throughout the Middle East."  Israeli left-wing activists protested against the war in Gaza and Lebanon outside the Israeli Defence Ministry in Tel Aviv on Sunday. The demonstration took place as Israel continued to bombard Gaza, while also engaging in a conflict with Hezbollah in Lebanon and recently launching air strikes against Iran. title: Israeli Protesters Demand Gaza Ceasefire After Lebanon Truce | Subscribe to Firstpost
description: Israeli Protesters Demand Gaza Ceasefire After Lebanon Truce | Subscribe to Firstpost  Israelis continued to demonstrate in Tel Aviv, urging action to secure the release of hostages taken during the October 7 attack, as the government approved a ceasefire deal with Hezbollah in Lebanon. title: Hamas Releases Video Of Teen Israeli Hostage, Her Parents React | Subscribe to Firstpost
description: Hamas Releases Video Of Teen Israeli Hostage, Her Parents React | Subscribe to Firstpost  Hamas on January 5 released an undated video of a 19-year-old Israeli hostage held in Gaza since its October 2023 attack. The three-and-a-half-minute video showed Liri Albag, who served as an Israeli soldier prior to October 7, 2023. The Hostages and Missing Families Forum, a campaign group for relatives of those abducted, said Albag's family has not authorised the publication of the video. "We appeal to the prime minister, world leaders and all decision-makers: it's time to take decisions as if it were your own children there," the family later said in a statement.  ---  Israel Hamas War | Israeli Hostages | Protest | Tel Aviv | Hostage Deal | Hamas | Ceasefire | Qatar | Benjamin Netanyahu | Palestine | West Asia | Firstpost | News Live | World News | Latest News | Global News | International News | News | Trending News  #israelhamaswar #israelihostages #protest #telaviv #hostagesituation #hamas #ceasefire #qatar #benjaminnetanyahu #palestine #westasia #firstpost #newslive #worldnews #latestnews #globalnews #news #internationalnews #trendingnews  Firstpost is an Indian news and media website. title: Hamas Gunakan Metode Tempur Baru di Gaza, 'Bom Perut' Beraksi, Ranjau Jadi Ancaman Besar Israel
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM- Pejuang Hamas dilaporkan menggunakan metode baru dalam pertempuran mereka untuk melawan Pasukan Pertahanan Israel (IDF).  IDF kini harus menghadapi ancaman besar di Gaza, yakni ranjau darat.  Ranjau-ranjau itu disebut Askhenazi sebagai â€œbelly bombâ€ atau â€œbom perutâ€.  Informasi itu diungkapkan Avi Askhenazi, seorang kolumnis pada surat kabar Israel Maariv.  Menurut Askhenazi, tentara Israel telah mendeteksi adanya perubahan cara berperang Hamas, terutama di Gaza bagian utara.  Mengutip Tribunnews pada (10/1/2025), Hamasmulai memasang lebih banyak ranjau darat di bawah tanah.  IDF memperkirakan Hamas akan lebih suka menyerang IDF dengan senjata yang ditinggalkan tentara Israel di lapangan.  Bom itu diaktifkan dengan remot kontrol ketika Hamas mendeteksi adanya pergerakan pasukan dari jarak jauh.  (Tribun-Video.com/ Palestinechronicle)  Hamas Shifts Tactics: Use of Underground Explosives Escalates in Gaza, West Bank https://www.palestinechronicle.com/hamas-shifts-tactics-use-of-underground-explosives-escalates-in-gaza-west-bank/  Program: Live Update  Host: Yustina Kartika Gati Editor Video: Ika Vidya Lestari Uploader: Restu Riyawan  #hamas #alqassambrigades #alqassambrigadesattack #israel #idf #palestina #palestine #gaza

Dozens of Israelis protest in Jerusalem against Gaza ceasefire deal
description: "This terrorist is a terrorist that is going to be released if we sign this deal. We can't have people like this walking around, whether it's Gaza, Israel, Europe, I don't care where. These terrorists need to be either killed or in a cell for the rest of their life."  Dozens of Israelis gathered at one of the entrances to Jerusalemâ€™s Old City to protest against a Gaza ceasefire deal as talks of it being near have increased in recent days.  Since the beginning of this year, negotiations mediated by Qatar, Egypt and the United States resumed in Doha to propose a ceasefire deal that would also facilitate the release of dozens of hostages still held in Gaza. The US has hinted that a deal could be reached before Biden leaves office on 20 January. description: Israeli Military Chief Resigns Over October 7 Massacre  Israeli military chief Herzi Halevi resigned on Tuesday over his "failure" to manage Hamas' attack on October 7, 2023. title: Defense minister confirms army orders to kill Israelis on 7 October

Questioning Gallant, journalist Amit Segal clarified for viewers that â€œthe Hannibal Directive says to shoot to kill when there is a vehicle containing an Israeli hostageâ€ â€“ a characterization Gallant did not contest.  Gallant was speaking in his first interview with Israeli television since being fired in November. title: Israeli hostage kisses heads of Hamas members during release
description: Released Israeli hostage Omer Shem Tov kisses the heads of Hamas members before being handed over to the International Red Cross as part of the seventh prisoner swap in Gazaâ€™s Nuseirat.  Shem Tov was released alongside Eliya Cohen and Omer Wenkert, bringing the total of released hostages to five on February 22.  A sixth hostage is expected to be released soon, reportedly without ceremony, in Gaza City. title: Thousands of Israelis protest the end of the ceasefire in Gaza
description: Thousands have taken to the streets in Israel to protest the collapse of the ceasefire with Hamas in Gaza, and to call for restarting talks to release the remaining hostages. The protests come after Israel killed more than 400 Palestinians and injured hundreds more in a series of surprise overnight airstrikes in Gaza early Tuesday.

title: Thousands of Israelis protest against resumption of Gaza war
description: Thousands of Israelis have been protesting against the decision by Benjamin Netanyahuâ€™s government to resume airstrikes on Gaza. Subscribe to Guardian News on YouTube â–º http://bit.ly/guardianwiressub  The protesters fear the resumption of the war will endanger the release of the remaining hostages held by Hamas. Fifty-nine hostages are yet to be released, of whom 24 are believed to be alive. The decision to resume the war has added fresh momentum to anti-government rallies, with protesters accusing Netanyahu's administration of continuing the conflict for political reasons. The recent airstrikes have killed more than 400 Palestinians and shattered the ceasefire agreement  Israeli strikes on Gaza add to soaring child death toll â–º https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/mar/20/israel-strikes-gaza-child-death-toll  Netanyahu is waging war on Gaza and on us â€“ his â€˜enemies withinâ€™. title: Tens of thousands of Israelis rally for hostages, protest dismissal of Shin Bet chief
description: Tens of thousands of Israelis protested on Saturday, demanding an end to the Gaza war to protect the lives of Israeli captives while opposing the dismissal of Shin Bet chief Ronen Bar.  Demonstrations took place in cities across the country, including Tel Aviv, Jerusalem, Haifa and Beersheba, with protesters blocking roads.  Netanyahuâ€™s decision to dismiss Bar, despite a Supreme Court freeze, sparked political tensions. Meanwhile, Israel's resumption of the war in Gaza has led to over 700 Palestinians being killed since Tuesday and nearly 50,000 since October 2023.

title: Jordanians protest for Gaza in Amman
description: Jordanians demonstrated in solidarity with Palestine after Friday prayers on 11 April.  Activists called for a march to the Jordan Valley, separating Jordan and the occupied West Bank, in protest of Israel's renewed war on Gaza.  War resumed after Israel failed to advance the ceasefire to phase two in early March, instead blocking all aid into Gaza and continuing its assault on the strip by air and ground.  Since then, Israel has announced "no go zones" in two-thirds of Gaza's territory, forcing hundreds of thousands of Palestinians to move elsewhere once again despite having nowhere to go. title: Douglas Murray remembers chilling October 7 call from Hamas
description: Douglas Murray discusses his reaction to details that emerged from the October 7th massacre, sharing the example of a young Hamas terrorist who called his parents in Gaza to proudly announce he had murdered 10 Jews.  Douglas says the 'wild glee' and 'worship of death' in the attackers' actions, and the fact this was not an isolated incident, highlights the profound difference between those who cherish life and those who revel in death.  With Spectator editor Michael Gove, Douglas explores the inspiration behind his book On Democracies and Death Cults: Israel, Hamas and the Future of the West, the significance of the October 7th attack, the characterisation of Hamas and Israel in Western media, and the lessons Britain can learn from Israel. Spectator subscribers can watch the full video online https://www.spectator.co.uk/douglas-murray-live   #DouglasMurray #Israel #October7th #MiddleEastConflict #hamas

title: Protesters gather in Tel Aviv, demanding end to war on Gaza
description: Hundreds of protesters gathered in Tel Aviv on Thursday, calling for an end to the war on Gaza as they held pictures of children killed due to Israeli bombings.  Since Israel broke the ceasefire deal on 18 March, around 2,000 Palestinians have been killed and 5,200 others have been wounded. title: Tampang 4 Tentara IDF Merintih Kesakitan Ditembak Sniper Hamas, Tersungkur & Angkat Tangan
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Brigade Al Qassam kembali menembaki gerombolan Pasukan Pertahanan Israel (IDF).   Penembakan dari jarak dekat itu diunggah di Telegram Al Qassam pada Sabtu (26/4).   Dinarasikan sniper Al Qassam menargetkan empat tentara IDF, yang satu di antaranya adalah seorang perwira.   Adapun penembakan itu terjadi di salah satu pos yang baru didirikan IDF di Beit Hanoun.   Terlihat, tentara IDF itu ditembak secara bergantian hingga tersungkur.   Wajah tentara Israel pun merintis kesakitan. title: Families of Israeli hostages in Gaza rally outside US embassy in Tel Aviv
description: (14 May 2025)  RESTRICTION SUMMARY:  ASSOCIATED PRESS Tel Aviv, Israel â€“ 13 May 2025 ++NIGHT SHOTS/QUALITY AS INCOMING++ 1.  Families of hostages and supporters gathered outside the U.S Embassy in Tel Aviv, holding U.S. flags and chanting UPSOUND (English) â€œBring them home nowâ€ 2.  Protesters marching  3.  Protesters holding banner reading (English): â€œPresident Trump, end the war - leave no hostage behind.â€ 4. SOUNDBITE (English) Yehuda Cohen, father of hostage Nimrod Cohen: ++PARTIALLY OVERLAID BY SHOT 5++ â€œ(U.S.) President Donald Trump, Special envoys to the Middle East, Steve Witkoff and Adam Boehler, we put all of our trust in you. We put all our trust in the American administration to force (Israeli Prime Minister, Benjamin) Netanyahu and his traitors government to go to a ceasefire, a permanent ceasefire, end the war and to a hostage deal.â€ 5. Protesters holding photos of hostages 6. Protesters marching   STORYLINE: Families of hostages and their supporters rallied on Tuesday outside the U.S embassy in Tel Aviv, calling on President Donald Trump to help bring about a deal that would see the release of the remaining captives still being held in Gaza.  It comes as Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Tuesday there was â€œno wayâ€ Israel will halt its war in Gaza â€” where airstrikes on two hospitals Tuesday killed at least eight and wounded dozens â€” even if a deal is reached to release more hostages.  Netanyahu's comments are likely to complicate talks on a new ceasefire that had seemed to gain momentum after Hamas released the last living American hostage on Monday in a gesture to Trump, who is visiting the region but skipping Israel.  They pointed to a potentially widening rift between Netanyahu and Trump, who had expressed hope that the release of Israeli-American soldier Edan Alexander would be a step toward ending the 19-month war.  In comments released by Netanyahu's office Tuesday from a visit to wounded soldiers the previous day, the prime minister said Israeli forces were just days away from a promised escalation of force and would enter Gaza â€œwith great strength to complete the mission. ... It means destroying Hamas.â€  Any ceasefire deal reached would be temporary, the prime minister said.   If Hamas were to say they would release more hostages, â€œweâ€™ll take them, and then weâ€™ll go in. But there will be no way we will stop the war,â€ Netanyahu said.  â€œWe can make a ceasefire for a certain period of time, but weâ€™re going to the end.â€  Hamas has said it will only release the remaining hostages in return for more Palestinian prisoners, a lasting ceasefire and an Israeli withdrawal from Gaza.   The dispute over whether to end the conflict has been the main obstacle in negotiations going back more than a year.  Israel says 58 hostages remain in captivity, with as many as 23 of them said to be alive, although authorities have expressed concern about the condition of three of them.   Many of the 250 hostages taken by Hamas-led militants in the October 7, 2023 attack that started the war were freed in ceasefire deals.  AP video shot by Moshe Edri   ===========================================================  Clients are reminded to adhere to all listed restrictions and to check the terms of their licence agreements. title: Gazaâ€™s Youngest Influencer Killed In Israeli Airstrike
description: Yaqeen Hammad was reported to have been killed after airstrikes on Deir al-Balah in the north of the strip on May 23, as Israel intensified its bombardment and ground offensive in Gaza.  Read more: https://www.thetimes.com/world/middle-east/israel-hamas-war/article/gaza-influencer-dies-video-yaqeen-hammad-0h8ds8rxv  The 11-year-old posted videos on social media to share humanitarian updates and survival tips from Gaza.   Yaqeen's death is one of more than 15,000 children reported killed in Gaza since the war began in October 2023, according to local health authorities. title: Paris Protest Turns Fountain Red to Demand Gaza Ceasefire | GRAVITAS
description: In a powerful protest in central Paris, activists and major NGOs dyed the Fountain of the Innocents red to symbolize the bloodshed in Gaza. With banners, smoke flares, and urgent demands for a ceasefire, they called on French President Emmanuel Macron and world leaders to take immediate action. title: Families of Israeli hostages mark 600 days since October 7 attack
description: Thousands of Israelis took part in protests around the country calling for a deal to be reached to return remaining hostages in Gaza, marking 600 days since the October 7 Hamas attack.  "There's a deal here waiting for us just to happen, but we need that extra push," said the father of hostage Itay Chen, who is believed to have been killed.  Of the 58 hostages that Hamas still holds, about 20 are believed to be alive. It comes as the Gaza health ministry said Wednesday at least 3,924 people had been killed in the territory since Israel broke the ceasefire on 18 March, taking the war's overall toll to more than 54,000, mostly civilians. title: Eight injured in incendiary device attack at rally for Israeli hostages in Boulder, Colorado
description: A man has been charged with multiple felonies after he allegedly used a makeshift flamethrower and incendiary devices to attack a crowd of people who were raising awareness for Israeli hostages in Gaza, injuring eight. Subscribe to Guardian News on YouTube â–º http://bit.ly/guardianwiressub  Mohamed Sabry Soliman, 45, is alleged to have shouted â€œFree Palestineâ€ as he attacked the crowd on Sunday, in what the FBI is treating as an â€œact of terrorismâ€.  Boulder police chief Stephen Redfearn said the department received calls at about 1.26pm local time on Sunday of a man with a weapon near a downtown courthouse and that people were being set on fire.  Four women and four men between 52 and 88 years old were transported to hospitals, police said, with injuries ranging from minor to â€œvery seriousâ€.  â€œIt is clear that this is a targeted act of violence, and the FBI is investigating this as an act of terrorism,â€ Mark Michalek, an FBI special agent, told a press conference, citing witnesses. He added that there was no evidence that the man was connected to a wider group.  Soliman was booked into Boulder county jail on Sunday and has a hearing scheduled for 1.30pm local time on Monday.  To read the latest on this story tap the link â–º  https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2025/jun/02/donald-trump-tariffs-white-house-us-politics-live-news

title: Thousands gather in London to protest Israel's war on Gaza
description: Thousands are marching in London to demand the UK government stop sending arms to Israel as it continues its deadly war on Gaza, and to bomb Iran.  The UK government approved $169m worth of military equipment to Israel in the three months that followed the Labour governmentâ€™s partial suspension of arms exports over concerns they could be used unlawfully in Gaza.  Government export data released in May shows that 20 different licences in categories such as military aircraft, radars, targeting equipment, and explosive devices, were approved between October and December 2024.  Arms campaigners say the three-month total is more than what was approved altogether under the Tory government between 2020 and 2023, and said the increase was â€œtruly shockingâ€. title: Israeli protesters urge action for Gaza hostages after Iran ceasefire
description: Families of hostages and former captives gathered in Tel Aviv, calling for immediate action. Among them was Liri Albag, who had been previously held in Gaza.  She urged Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and US President Donald Trump to act decisively, praising the recent ceasefire with Iran and calling for a similar breakthrough in Gaza. â€œYou made a brave decision on Iran. Now make a brave decision to end the war in Gaza and bring them all home - now.â€  The protest follows President Trumpâ€™s claim that a ceasefire between Israel and Hamas could be reached within a week. title: Germany's ambassador to Israel joins rally to release hostages, calls for end to war in Gaza
description: (4 Jul 2025)  RESTRICTION SUMMARY:  ASSOCIATED PRESS Netanya, Israel -  3 July 2025 1. Various of demonstrators holding banners with photographs of their loved ones who were killed or are held hostages 2. SOUNDBITE (Hebrew) Steffen Seibert, Germany's ambassador to Israel: "It's clear that only a deal is the surest way to bring the hostages home. That's how it worked in the past and it can work again. Not a war that goes on forever, but a deal with all the difficulty of closing a deal with Hamas." 3. Various of demonstrators listening to speakers and holding banners STORYLINE: Germany's ambassador to Israel Steffen Seibert joined Israeli families on Thursday at a rally in Netanya, Israel to demand the release of the remaining hostages in Gaza.  "It's clear that only a deal is the surest way to bring the hostages home," said Seibert.   He also called to end the in war in Gaza "to prevent more young Israeli soldiers from falling in the ruins of Gaza, and to free hundreds of thousands of civilians in Gaza from the terrible reality they have been living in for 20 months."  Seibert joined dozens of Israeli demonstrators and the family of Italy Chen, an Israeli-American and German soldier who was killed in the Hamas attack on Oct. 7.    Chen's family doesnâ€™t have a grave to visit because his remains are still held captive in Gaza.   "The Middle East is at an inflection point where we see opportunity with Lebanon, Syria, Saudi Arabia and now is the time to cement the military victories on Hamas," Italy's father Ruby Chen told the Associated Press.  On Wednesday, US President Donald Trump said Israel has agreed on terms for a new 60-day ceasefire with Hamas and that Washington would work with both sides during that time to try to end more than 20 months of war in Gaza.  Neither side has accepted the proposal announced on Tuesday by Trump, who has admonished Hamas that if the militant group does not buy into the offer, its prospects will get worse.   Itâ€™s not clear what conditions Israel agreed to.  The efforts to reach a truce are unfolding in the wake of powerful Israeli and American strikes on nuclear sites in Iran, which has long supported Hamas and just days before Trump is scheduled to meet with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in Washington.  AP Video by Fernanda Pesce  ===========================================================  Clients are reminded to adhere to all listed restrictions and to check title: Pejuang Hamas Nyamar Jadi Prajurit Israel, Saat Lengah Lesatkan Tembakan Maut & Tewaskan Puluhan IDF
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Pejuang Hamas dilaporkan menyamar sebagai prajurit IDF dan berhasil menyusup posisi militer Israel tanpa terdeteksi.  Saat pasukan Zionis lengah, mereka melepaskan tembakan maut menewaskan puluhan tentara di Gaza.  Aksi penyamaran ini terekam dalam video yang dirilis Brigade Al-Qassam pada Jumat (11/7/2025), memperlihatkan keberadaan Hamas di sekitar posisi IDF.   (Al-Mayadeen.net)  Program: Tribunnews Update Host: Anggraheni Widya Witari Editor: Mellinia Pranandari Uploader: Tri Hantoro  #israel #gaza #hamas #palestina #idf

title: Israelis burn their military draft papers to protest war in Gaza #shorts

title: Jordanians protest Gaza war
description: Crowds took to the streets of Amman's Tafilah neighbourhood in Jordan to protest Israel's ongoing war on Gaza.  Many were highly critical of the Jordanian government's failure to end the war, saying "we too are besieged" in reference to King Abdullah II's failure to align with popular attitudes on the issue.  Since the war's outbreak, Jordan has helped Israel intercept Iranian missiles launched toward its territory. Throughout this time, recurring protests in Amman and elsewhere in the country have called for an end to Jordan's 1994 peace treaty with Israel. title: Israeli police crack down as thousands protest Gaza war
description: Police cracked down on protesters in Tel Aviv, using mounted units to disperse crowds demanding an end to the Gaza war.  Protesters blocked several streets across the city after the main demonstration in Habima Square.   The anti-war demonstrators were calling for political accountability and a ceasefire.  #israel #gaza #palestine

title: Hamas Kian Berjaya di Gaza hingga Prajurit Israel Frustasi Tembak Mati Komandannya Sendiri
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Seorang perwira tinggi militer Israel (IDF) dilaporkan tewas setelah ditembak oleh pasukannya sendiri saat operasi di Jalur Gaza.  Dikutip dari Al Mayadeen, Senin (28/7), ribuan tentara Israel dilaporkan tewas dalam pertempuran sengit di Gaza akibat serangan pejuang Palestina.  Tak hanya itu, kekacauan di medan perang juga menyebabkan insiden salah tembak antar pasukan sendiri.  (Tribun-Video/Almayadeen.net)  Artikel ini telah tayang di Almayadeen.net dengan judul Tentara Israel tewas, sembilan lainnya luka-luka dalam operasi Khan Younis, https://english.almayadeen.net/news/politics/israeli-soldier-killed--nine-wounded-in-khan-younis-operatio  Program: Tribunnews Update Host: Anggraheni Widya Witari Editor: Nur Rohman Urip Uploader: Bintang Nur Rahman

title: Gaza protesters confront Israeli cruise ship docked in Crete
description: Protesters waving Palestinian flags scuffled with police at Agios Nikolaos port in Crete, Greece, where an Israeli cruise ship was docked. It was the third such protest to take place in the Greek islands in a week after similar scenes in Rhodes and Syros. Subscribe to Guardian News on YouTube â–º http://bit.ly/guardianwiressub  In recent years, Greece has become a popular destination for Israeli tourists, reflecting the increasingly close ties between the two Mediterranean nations. title: Protesters rally for 3rd time as Israeli cruise ship docks in Greece
description: Protesters against the war in Gaza rallied yet again as a cruise ship with Israeli tourists docked on the island of Crete Tuesday. Police fired tear gas after scuffles broke out and three people were detained and later released. This is the third such protest of the same cruise ship on the Greek islands since last week.   #Greece #Crete #Palestinian #Israel #Gaza

title: Israelis Rally After Hamas Footage Shows Hostages' Declining Health Due To Starvation In Gaza
description: Families of Israeli hostages held by Hamas staged a protest in Tel Aviv on August 2, calling for a ceasefire and the immediate return of their loved ones.  The protest on Saturday morning at the iconic Hostages Square was called after Hamas released a video of hostage Evyatar David in one of its tunnels appearing skeletally thin.  The protesters held up banners and photographs of hostages, urging Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to finalise a deal. title: Ignored Warnings: The Truth Behind October 7th
description: October 7th is often described as a day of shocking savagery, but a deeper investigation reveals a different narrative. Evidence mounts that the events leading up to this date were not unforeseen; instead, numerous warnings from Israeli surveillance units, particularly young female soldiers manning outposts along the Gaza border, indicated preparations by Hamas for an assault. From live fire training to trench digging, these alerts were detailed and time-sensitive but tragically overlooked. The stakes were raised by Egypt's General Intelligence Directorate, which issued a clear warning just three days before the attack. Did Israel's leadership misjudge the situation, or was there a conscious decision to ignore critical intelligence? The investigation into this troubling oversight raises important questions that demand answers. #October7 #Hamas #Israel #IntelligenceFail #WarReports #MiddleEast #CurrentEvents #shorts

title: Today in Australia: Over 100K March for Gaza, Shut Down Major Bridge
description: Over a hundred thousand protesters shut down the Sydney Harbour Bridge today to stand against the U.S.-Israeli genocide and forced starvation in Gaza.  Pressure is mounting against the U.S.-Israeli occupation as global demonstrations have forced countries like the UK, France, Canada, and Malta to announce they will recognize Palestinian statehood at the UN General Assembly next month.

title: Hamas Izinkan Israel Beri Bantuan ke Warganya yang Ditahan di Gaza, Asal Penuhi Syarat Ini
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM- Hamas mengaku siap berkoordinasi bersama Palang Merah untuk mengirimkan bantuan kepada para sandera yang ditahannya di Gaza.  Dikutip dari The Guardian (4/8/2025), Hamas bersedia melakukan itu asal Israel memenuhi syarat yang diberikan.  Syarat dari Hamas adalah Israel menghentikan serangan udara selama penyaluran bantuan di Gaza.   Hamas juga meminta Israel membuka permanen koridor kemanusiaan di Gaza.  Hal ini terjadi setelah video yang dirilis Hamas menunjukkan seorang sandera bernama Evyatar David, warga Israel yang ditahan di Hamas kurus kering.  David terlihat sedang menggali lubang yang menurutnya dalam video tersebut, dimaksudkan untuk kuburannya sendiri.  Video itu menuai kritik tajam dari sejumlah negara Barat.  Dilansir Reuters, Senin (4/8/2025), menurut pejabat Israel, 50 sandera kini masih berada di Gaza.  Namun, hanya 20 orang yang diyakini masih hidup.  Hamas sejauh ini melarang organisasi kemanusiaan untuk mengakses para sandera.  Keluarga mereka pun hanya memiliki sedikit atau bahkan tidak ada informasi mengenai kondisi mereka.  Sementara itu sebelumnya, Perdana Menteri Israel Benjamin Netanyahu meminta palang merah untuk memberikan bantuan kemanusiaan kepada para sandera.  (Tribun-Video.com/ Theguardian.com)  Artikel ini telah tayang dengan judul, Hamas releases second video of Israeli hostage and says it will not disarm until Palestinian state established https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/aug/03/israel-gaza-war-hamas-releases-second-video-of-hostage  Program: Live Update Host: Yustina Kartika Gati Editor: Agilio OktoViasta Uploader: Restu Riyawan  #Israel #zionis #Hamas #Palestina #Gaza #TahananIsrael #BantuanKemanusiaan #BeritaTerkini #KonflikIsraelPalestina #HamasIsrael #BeritaInternasional #UpdateGaza

title: Drone footage reveals scale of historic Sydney Gaza solidarity protest
description: Drone footage has captured the moment Australian demonstrators flooded Sydneyâ€™s central districts and spanned the Harbour Bridge in a massive protest against Israelâ€™s brutal war in Gaza.  The historic turnout, organised under the â€œMarch for Humanityâ€ banner, was initially denied permission by the New South Wales premier and police authorities, but a court order gave last-minute approval.  Despite short notice and adverse weather conditions, the rally brought together an estimated 300,000 people.  Demonstrators chanted â€œFree Palestineâ€ and waved flags and placards calling for a ceasefire, an end to the blockade of Gaza, and for Australian authorities to sanction Israel.  Organisers said the massive turnout reflected growing global outrage over the rising civilian death toll in Gaza and the international communityâ€™s failure to prevent a deepening humanitarian catastrophe. title: Israeli protesters rally at Netanyahu's office demanding Gaza ceasefire
description: Israeli protesters rallied outside Benjamin Netanyahu's office in Jerusalem on Monday, 4 August, calling to end the war in Gaza, return all hostages under a comprehensive deal, and cancel the motion to sack attorney general Gali Baharav-Miara.  Demonstrators gathered outside the building while the Israeli cabinet was set to vote on firing Ms Baharav-Miara, who has sparred with Netanyahu's cabinet over the legality of some of its policies.  The High Court of Israel issued a temporary order blocking the governmentâ€™s attempt to dismiss Ms Baharav-Miara.  Israel's government has been seeking the dismissal of Ms Baharav-Miara for months.  Footage shows protesters holding photos of hostages and signs calling to end the war in Gaza. title: At least 40 arrested at protest against Gaza war at Trump hotel in New York
description: Hundreds of people gathered in New York to protest against Israel's war on Gaza and demand that the Trump administration put pressure on Benjamin Netanyahu to allow more humanitarian aid into Gaza. Subscribe to Guardian News on YouTube â–º http://bit.ly/guardianwiressub  The protest, organised by IfNotNow, a Jewish-American anti-occupation group, began at Columbus Circle and ended outside the Trump International hotel were several people were arrested for blocking the road. title: Ribuan Warga Israel Pawai Ingin Pindah ke Gaza, Sebut Sudah Kosong dari Orang Palestina dan Hamas
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Sejumlah warga Israel dan kelompok sayap kanan menggelar pawai di dekat perbatasan Gaza pada awal Agustus 2025.  Menyerukan pembangunan kembali permukiman Yahudi di wilayah yang hancur akibat serangan militer Israel.  Demonstran membawa poster bertuliskan â€œKembali ke Gazaâ€ dan menyebut bahwa Gaza kini telah â€œkosong dari warga Palestinaâ€.  Beberapa bahkan menyatakan, â€œTidak ada lagi Hamas, tidak ada lagi Palestina, hanya Israel.â€  Anggota parlemen dari Partai Zionisme Religius, Tzvi Sukkot, turut hadir dan mendukung gagasan pendudukan kembali Gaza oleh warga Yahudi.  Seruan ini muncul di tengah krisis kemanusiaan di Gaza, yang menewaskan lebih dari 3.000 warga Palestina dan menghancurkan ribuan rumah.   Pernyataan tersebut memicu kekhawatiran internasional atas potensi pendudukan baru di wilayah tersebut.  Artikel ini telah tayang di Kompas.com dengan judul "Ribuan Warga Israel Ingin Pindah ke Gaza, Sebut Sudah Kosong dari Orang Palestina", Klik untuk baca: https://www.kompas.com/global/read/2025/08/05/125214070/ribuan-warga-israel-ingin-pindah-ke-gaza-sebut-sudah-kosong-dari-orang.  Program: Tribunnews Update Host: Tita Syarif Editor: Ni'amu Shoim Assari Alfani Uploader: Tri Hantoro  #israel #palestine

title: Israel: Police Clash With Tel Aviv Protesters Demanding Gaza Hostagesâ€™ Release | N18G
description: Israel: Police Clash With Tel Aviv Protesters Demanding Gaza Hostagesâ€™ Release | N18G  Israeli police clashed with protesters in Tel Aviv on August 7 during a rally demanding the release of hostages held by Hamas in Gaza and an end to the war. Officers used water cannons to disperse demonstrators who lit flares, chanted slogans, and displayed banners of those still captive. The protest was part of growing public pressure on the Israeli government. title: Balcony collapses in Gaza under weight of crowd scrambling for aid
description: As Palestinians rushed toward an aid package airdropped in Gaza City, a balcony collapsed under the weight of the crowd. It is not clear how many people were injured in this incident. #CNN #news #Gaza

title: Kehabisan Tentara! Israel Rekrut Prajurit Tua untuk Maju Perang Lawan Hamas di Gaza, Kalah Kekuatan?
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru      TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Hampir dua tahun berperang, militer mulai kekurangan prajurit untuk bertempur di Jalur Gaza melawan pasukan perlawanan Palestina, Hamas.  Dikutip dari SerambiNews.com, Sabtu (9/8/2025), Militer Israel (IDF) disebut mengambil sejumlah langkah tak biasa demi mengatasi persoalan tersebut.  IDF Dilaporkan menyetujui pembentukan satuan cadangan yang beranggotakan tentara berusia di atas 50 tahun. (SerambiNews.com/Teuku Raja M)  Artikel ini telah tayang di SerambiNews.com dengan judul VIDEO - Stok Tentara Menipis, IDF Rekrut Lansia di Atas 50 Tahun Tuai Polemik, https://aceh.tribunnews.com/2025/08/08/video-stok-tentara-menipis-idf-rekrut-lansia-di-atas-50-tahun-tuai-polemik.  Program: Tribunnews Update Host: Tri Suhartini Editor: Nathanael Moer Rahardian Uploader: Tri Hantoro      #Israel #PrajuritTua #PerangGaza #Hamas #KekuranganTentara #BrigadeHasmonean #KonflikTimurTengah #IDF #MiliterIsrael #Perang

title: Pro-Palestine activists march in London against Israelâ€™s war on Gaza
description: Pro-Palestine activists are marching in London to protest against Israelâ€™s war on Gaza, its blockade of aid to the enclave and policy of forced starvation, as well as its recent announcement that it will intensify its military assault and Israelâ€™s security cabinetâ€™s approval of a plan to occupy the Gaza Strip. Demonstrators are calling on the UK government to impose a full military embargo on Israel, end all military cooperation, suspend trade, and take concrete action to stop the war on Gaza. title: Anti-government protesters march in Israel as families call for release of hostages
description: Relatives and supporters of Israeli hostages held in the Gaza Strip attended their weekly rally in Tel Aviv Saturday, demanding their release from Hamas captivity and calling for an end to the war. Also in Tel Aviv, thousands of anti-government protesters marched on Saturday in what was one of the largest gatherings in the city since the beginning of Israel's war with Hamas.    #israel #gaza   Subscribe: http://smarturl.it/AssociatedPress Read more: https://apnews.comâ€‹  This video may be available for archive licensing via https://newsroom.ap.org/home

title: Israel: Air Force Reservists and Former Pilots Rally in Tel Aviv to End Gaza War | N18G
description: Israel: Air Force Reservists and Former Pilots Rally in Tel Aviv to End Gaza War | N18G  Former Israeli Air Force pilots and reservists gathered outside military headquarters in Tel Aviv on Tuesday, calling for an end to the war in Gaza and the safe return of hostages. Demonstrators carried Israeli flags and yellow flags symbolising hostages, including images of an ex-pilot missing in Lebanon since 1986. title: Tak Mampu Ditepis, Benteng Terakhir Israel di Gaza Luluhlantak Dihujani Rudal 'Taring' Hamas
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Hamas melancarkan serangan dahsyat menargetkan benteng terakhir Israel di Gaza, Jumat (15/8).  Rudal-rudal canggih mendarat tepat sasaran, menimbulkan kehancuran hebat dan korban di pihak Israel.  Hamas menggunakan rentetan rudal canggih Al-Yasin 105 menghantam dua rumah tempat tentara Israel berlindung, bahkan tank merkava juga menjadi sasaran empuk para pejuang Palestina. (Khaberni.com)  Artikel ini telah tayang di Khaberni.com dengan judul Perlawanan menargetkan kendaraan dan pasukan Israel di lingkungan Zeitoun di Gaza selatan, https://www.khaberni.com/news/726962-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%81-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%88%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%AD%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%86-%D8%AC%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A8-%D8%BA%D8%B2%D8%A9  Program: Tribunnews Update Host: Anggraheni Widya Witari Editor: Mellinia Pranandari Uploader: bagus gema praditiya sukirman  #israel #gaza #hamas #palestina #idf #tentaraidf #alqassambrigades

title: Anti-war protests across Israel
description: Thousands of Israelis took part in a nationwide strike on Sunday in support of families of hostages held in Gaza, holding demonstrations calling on Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu to reach an agreement with Hamas to end the war and release the remaining captives.  Protesters waved Israeli flags and carried photos of hostages as whistles, horns, and drums echoed at rallies across the country, while some blocked streets and highways, including the main route between Jerusalem and Tel Aviv.  In response, Netanyahu told the cabinet: "Those who call today for an end to the war without defeating Hamas are not only hardening Hamas' position and delaying the release of our hostages, they are also ensuring that the horrors of October 7 will repeat themselves over and over again."  #israel #gaza #palestine #protest

title: Actor Gal Gadot Shows Solidarity with Israeli Hostages Families on Strike Day | Israel Gaza | N18G
description: Actor Gal Gadot visited hostages square in Tel Aviv on Sunday (August 17) to show her support for the families of Israeli hostages still held in Gaza. Thousands of Israelis took part in a nationwide strike on Sunday in support of families of hostages held in Gaza, calling on Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who leads the country's most right-wing government in history, to reach an agreement with Hamas to end the war and release the remaining captives. Demonstrators waved Israeli flags and carried photos of hostages as whistles, horns, and drums echoed at rallies across the country. Some protesters blocked streets and highways, including the main route between Jerusalem and Tel Aviv. According to Israeli police, 38 demonstrators had been detained by 2 p.m. local time (1100GMT). Some protesters blocking roads scuffled with police, and were carried away by officers. A major rally is scheduled to take place in Tel Aviv in the evening. The Israeli government has faced sharp criticism at home and abroad, including from some of its closest European allies, over the announcement that the military would soon seize Gaza City.  #galgadot #israelhostages #gaza #israelpalestineconflict #cnbctv18

title: Protests Erupt Across Israel As People Demand Immediate Ceasefire In Gaza
description: Protests Erupt Across Israel As People Demand Immediate Ceasefire In Gaza  On Sunday, large crowds across Israel held protests and strikes, calling for a ceasefire with Hamas to bring hostages home and end the war in Gaza. People blocked roads, held signs, and chanted in cities like Jerusalem, opposing the governmentâ€™s plan to expand the conflict. A group of hostage families led a nationwide strike, warning that more fighting would risk innocent lives. Protesters said many Israelis are against the war and want peace.
