title: Nationwide protests erupt in Israel to demand end of Gaza war
description: An estimated 500,000 people gathered in Tel Aviv on Sunday to call for an end to Israelâ€™s war in Gaza and the release of hostages in one of the largest protests in Israel since fighting began in October 2023. Subscribe â–º http://bit.ly/guardianwiressub Along the Green Line â–º https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=43oZ0yUDG8E&list=PLa_1MA_DEorGnakB7QV1Q_LBpHgtGQDxi  The rally on Sunday evening was the culmination of a day of nationwide protests and a general strike to pressure the government to halt the military campaign.  The Hostages and Missing Families Forum campaign group vowed protesters would â€œshut down the countryâ€, with the goal of bringing back the hostages and ending the war.  â€œWe demand a comprehensive and achievable agreement and an end to the war,â€ said Einav Zangauker, a leading figure of the protest movement whose son Matan is being held by Hamas in Gaza.  The protests came more than a week after Israelâ€™s security cabinet approved plans to capture Gaza City, 22 months into a war that has created a dire humanitarian crisis in the Palestinian territory.  Israelâ€™s military offensive has killed at least 61,000 Palestinians, according to Gazaâ€™s health ministry, most of them civilians. The figure does not include the thousands believed to be buried under rubble or the thousands killed indirectly as a consequence of the war.  The Israeli prime minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, criticised the protesters, saying their actions â€œnot only harden Hamasâ€™s position and draw out the release of our hostagesâ€, but also ensured that â€œthe horrors of 7 Octoberâ€ would reoccur.  #gaza #hamashostages #october7 #israelprotest #telaviv #telavivprotests #israelihostages #gazahostages #gazagenocide #gazawar #palestine #benjaminnetanyahu

title: Israelis Protest Netanyahu's Plan to Expand Gaza Operation
description: Hundreds of thousands of Israelis took to the streets on Sunday to protest Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahuâ€™s plan to expand operations in the Gaza Strip, rather than attempt to negotiate an end to the war under which Hamas would free its last hostages. #politics #israel #trump #netanyahu #gaza #worldnews #palestine #us #telaviv   Organizers said that as many as half a million people attended the main rally at Tel Avivâ€™s â€œhostage squareâ€ in the evening, a massive turnout by Israeli standards.  Earlier on Sunday, as Netanyahu suggested calls to end the war would embolden Hamas, police scuffled with demonstrators blocking roads across Israel, making at least 30 arrests and turning a water cannon on participants at a sit-down protest at a Jerusalem access tunnel. title: Mass rally in Tel Aviv calls for end to Gaza war, hostage deal
description: Tens of thousands of demonstrators gathered in Tel Aviv to call for an end to the war in Gaza and the release of hostages, one of the largest demonstrations in Israel since the start of the fighting in October 2023.  The rally was the culmination of a day of nationwide protests and a general strike to pressure the government to halt the military campaign. title: Israel Launches Next Phase in Gaza War as Hostage Protests Sweep Nation | VFI News
description: Israel has announced the next phase of the war against Hamas as the IDF launches Operation Gideonâ€™s Chariots with a sharpened focus on Gaza City. IDF Chief of Staff Lt.-Gen. Eyal Zamir declared that the army will continue its momentum until Hamas faces decisive defeat and emphasized that returning the hostages remains Israelâ€™s foremost priority. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu outlined a long-term plan for Israel to assume control in Gaza after Hamas is dismantled, mobilizing large reserve forces to carry out the mission. As the war escalates, grassroots voices inside Gaza are rising up against Hamas despite threats and repression, with educators, activists, and youth movements calling for peace and a post-Hamas future. Meanwhile, nationwide hostage protests swept across Israel, with nearly a million people gathering in Tel Avivâ€™s Hostages Square and strikes disrupting life from the Galilee to Eilat. Netanyahu and right-wing ministers condemned the demonstrations, while opposition leaders defended them as a moral imperative to secure the captivesâ€™ release. The political divide grows as Israel faces the dual challenge of defeating Hamas militarily and resolving the hostage crisis. At the same time, banks posted record wartime profits, the Cyprus president warned of Iranâ€™s nuclear threat, and Israel approved Indonesiaâ€™s humanitarian airdrop to Gaza. This update highlights the latest developments in Israelâ€™s war with Hamas, the hostagesâ€™ struggle, grassroots resistance in Gaza, and the broader regional stakes shaping the Middle East.  #Israel #GazaWar #Hamas #Hostages #MiddleEast  Visit: https://www.visionforisrael.com/en SUBSCRIBE TO GET NOTIFIED! https://www.youtube.com/c/VisionforIsrael?sub_confirmation=1  #VisionForIsrael #CrisisResponse #SupportingIsrael  Know about our VFI NEWS site? title: Israelis protest Gaza war, demand release of hostages | ABC NEWS
description: Thousands of Israelis have taken part in a nationwide strike, calling for the end of the war and the release the remaining captives. Fifty Israeli hostages remain in Gaza, with 20 believed to be alive. Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu criticised the protesters, saying they were strengthening Hamas and ensuring an endless war. title: Netanyahu Marah Didemo Ratusan Ribu Warganya, Tegaskan Tetap Bakal Teruskan Perang di Gaza
description: Baca Selengkapnya di https://video.tribunnews.com/view/858796/netanyahu-marah-didemo-ratusan-ribu-warganya-tegaskan-tetap-bakal-teruskan-perang-di-gaza  Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Perdana Menteri Israel Benjamin Netanyahu menegaskan enggan mengakhiri perang meski telah didemo ratusan ribu warganya di Tel Aviv pada Minggu (17/8).  Dilansir dari The Times of Israel, Netanyahu menyebut pihak yang menyerukan diakhirinya perang tanpa kekalahan Hamas sama dengan menunda pembebasan sandera.  Oleh karena itu ia tetap akan melanjutkan perang di Gaza bahkan memperluas agresinya. title: Hamas Agrees to 60-Day Ceasefire with Israel and a Hostage Release | N18G
description: Hamas Agrees to 60-Day Ceasefire with Israel and a Hostage Release | N18G  Hamas agreed to a 60-day ceasefire proposal with Israel, according to Egyptian officials. The deal included releasing half of the hostages held in Gaza in exchange for some Palestinian prisoners. Israel had already accepted a similar US-backed plan. The announcement came as Israeli forces moved to seize Gaza City, described by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu as Hamasâ€™ last stronghold. title: Hamas Survivors Join Protest to End War in Gaza
description: The families of Israeli hostages escalated their demonstrations to demand an end to the war in Gaza with a nationwide strike on Sunday, as the military forged ahead with its plans to push further into the territory.  READ MORE: https://www.thetimes.com/world/middle-east/israel-hamas-war/article/israeli-hostage-families-demand-end-to-war-in-gaza-qnkdqgjt7  Israeli police hit crowds with water cannon and arrested 38 people as hundreds of thousands gathered across the country, brandishing yellow flags and signs calling to save the 49 remaining hostages languishing in Hamas captivity for nearly two years.  Families of those freed, as well as those still captive, organised a day of marches towards Hostages Square in Tel Aviv, which has been the focal point of efforts to bring them home.  â€œI know first-hand what itâ€™s like to be in captivity. I know that military pressure doesnâ€™t bring hostages back, it only kills them. The only way to bring them back is through a deal, all at once, without games,â€ the released hostage Arbel Yehoud said, standing alongside fellow survivors including Yarden Bibas, whose wife and two children were murdered by their captors in Gaza, and flanked by Jewish Holocaust survivors.  The families drew parallels between the worst day in Israelâ€™s 77-year history, when Hamas militants killed and captured more than a thousand Israeli civilians and soldiers on October 7, 2023, and the genocide against Jews committed by the Nazis. They planned to stand on a mountain of ashes at what was set to be one of the largest gatherings since the start of the war. title: Thousands gather in Tel Aviv to honour the victims of October 7 Nova Festival
description: (15 Aug 2025)  RESTRICTION SUMMARY:  ASSOCIATED PRESS  Tel Aviv, Israel - 14 August 2025 1. Digital screen displaying photos of people killed at Nova festival on Oct. 7th, text reading (English) "We will never forget you, our angels in the sky."  2. SOUNDBITE (English) Joe Cohen, survivor of October 7th at the Nova festival: ++SOUNDBITE SPLIT SCREEN WITH SHOT1 AND IS PARTIALLY OVERLAID BY SHOT3++ "Being here at the healing concert for the second time is amazing, it is healing as you would call it, but most importantly it makes me feel hopeful that we will dance again." 3. Various of people, dancing  4. SOUNDBITE (English) Idan Bahat, father of Dror Bahat killed on October 7th at the Nova Festival: ++SOUNDBITE IS OVERLAID BY SHOT6 AND PARTIALLY BY SHOT6++ "Is it really healing? Well, not for us. Not for us. Nothing has changed, and we are still really, really expecting that someone will try to give us some answers." 5. Various of photos of hostages, text reading (Hebrew) "The people are with the hostages" 6. Various of survivors from Oct. 7th, 2023 Hamas attack on Nova music festival leading a moment of silence with thousands of people commemorating the attack ++NIGHT SHOTS++    STORYLINE: Survivors and thousands of others gathered in Tel Aviv on Thursday for the Nova Healing Concert to honour the victims of the October 7, 2023, Hamas attack on the Nova music festival.  More than 3,000 people were at the Tribe of Nova music festival on the morning of the attack when Hamas militants stormed into Israel. More than 300 people at the festival were killed.  One of the organizers said that the Nova Healing Concert was created to memorialize the people killed on October 7 and to bring the community together to heal.  â€œThe dance floor is supposed to be the safest place on earth," said Ofir Amir, a producer of the festival. "And through the dance floor, through dancing, through the music, we are healing together."  A survivor of the attack said the event helps her recover from the trauma of that day.  "It is healing as you would call it, but most importantly it makes me feel hopeful that we will dance again," said survivor Joe Cohen.  But not everyone feels the same.  Idan Bahat, father of Dror Bahat, who was killed at the Nova Festival, said his family is still suffering. His sonâ€™s body remains in Gaza, and the family continues to wait for answers about the attack.  â€œSo, is it really healing? Well, not for us. Not for us. Nothing has changed, and we are still really, really expecting that someone will try to give us some answers,â€ he said.  The war started when Hamas-led militants stormed into Israel on Oct. 7, 2023, killing around 1,200 people and abducting 251 people.  Israelâ€™s retaliatory campaign has killed more 61,700 Palestinians, according to Gazaâ€™s Health Ministry, which does not specify how many were fighters or civilians but says around half were women and children. Most of the hostages have been released in ceasefires or other deals but 50 remain inside Gaza. Israel believes around 20 of them to be alive.  The health ministry is part of the Hamas-run government and staffed by medical professionals.  AP Video by Paz Bar   ===========================================================  Clients are reminded to adhere to all listed restrictions and to check the terms of their licence agreements. For further assistance, please contact the AP Archive on: Tel +44(0)2074827482 Email: info@aparchive.com.  Find out more about AP Archive: http://www.aparchive.com/HowWeWork  Twitter: https://twitter.com/AP_Archive  Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/APArchives â€‹â€‹ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/APNews/   You can license this story through AP Archive: http://www.aparchive.com/metadata/youtube/84c00acbe5224363a135613eb65c9bb0

title: Pemukim Palestina Bergemuruh! Israel Angkat Tangan saat Hamas Diam diam Culik IDF hingga Dibunuh
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Brigade Al-Qassam, sayap militer Hamas, melancarkan operasi infiltrasi dan penculikan di pangkalan militer baru Israel dekat Khan Younis, Senin (20/8).  Insiden itu melibatkan sekira 14 hingga 20 pejuang Palestina,  berhasil menerobos pertahanan dan menyerang beberapa tank Merkava pasukan Zionis.  Hamas berhasil membidik rumah tempat IDF bersembunyi dengan tembakan jarak dekat. (Palestinechronicle.com)  Artikel ini telah tayang di Palestinechronicle.com dengan judul Brigade Al-Qassam Merinci Serangan Kompleks terhadap Pasukan Israel di Gaza, https://www.palestinechronicle.com/exceptional-incident-al-qassam-brigades-detail-complex-attack-on-israeli-forces-in-gaza/  Program: Tribunnews Update Host: Anggraheni Widya Witari Editor: Muhammad Adnan Hidayat Uploader: bagus gema praditiya sukirman

title: Detik-detik Video Tank Israel Tabrak Hamas dari Belakang hingga Tewas, Jasadnya Terkapar di Tanah
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  Pasukan pendudukan Israel mengaku berhasil membunuh sejumlah pasukan perlawanan Palestina, Hamas, Rabu (20/8/2025).  Juru Bicara IDF Brigjen Effie Defrin menyebut, jika awalnya ada sejumlah pasukan perlawanan yang memasuki gedung tempat istirahat mereka hingga terjadi baku tembak.  Tak hanya terlibat baku tembak, IDF juga membunuh Hamas dengan cara menabraknya dengan tank. (TheTimesofIsrael)  Artikel ini telah tayang di TheTimesofIsrael dengan judul "IDF mengatakan pasukannya berhasil menangkis serangan skala besar yang jarang terjadi di Gaza selatan; 10 pria bersenjata tewas", Klik untuk baca:   https://www.timesofisrael.com/idf-says-troops-repelled-rare-large-scale-attack-in-south-gaza-10-terrorists-killed/  Program: Tribunnews Update Host: Tri Suhartini Editor: Muhammad Taufiq Rahman Setyawan Uploader: bagus gema praditiya sukirman   #idf #hamas #palestina #gaza #israel #konfliktimurtengah #konflikisraelpalestina #zionis #netanyahu

title: Israel Begins First Stage Of Military Operation In Gaza City | Subscribe to Firstpost | N18G
description: Israel Begins First Stage Of Military Operation In Gaza City | Subscribe to Firstpost | N18G  Israel announced it had begun the first stage of a planned operation to seize Gaza City, with troops circling the outskirts. Military officials described Hamas as weakened but still active in clashes, including one near Khan Younis that wounded three Israeli soldiers. The army also called up tens of thousands of reservists in preparation for the offensive, even as international mediators worked on a ceasefire proposal. title: Footage of Qassam attack on â€˜Israeliâ€™ army in Khan Younis
description: Qassam Brigades, the armed wing of Hamas, announced on Wednesday that its fighters carried out a complex attack lasting several hours against a newly established 'Israeli' military site southeast of Khan Younis in southern Gaza.  In a statement, the Brigades said that a platoon-sized unit launched the raid by targeting several Merkava-4 guard tanks.  It added that fighters shelled houses where 'Israeli' soldiers were stationed with six anti-fortification rounds and heavy machine gun fire, before storming the buildings and engaging troops at close range with light weapons and hand grenades, claiming to have killed and wounded several soldiers.  The statement also said that a sniper targeted and fatally hit the commander of a Merkava-4 tank. When an 'Israeli' rescue unit arrived, one of the fighters detonated himself among the soldiers, causing further casualties.  To secure their withdrawal and block reinforcements, the fighters reportedly shelled surrounding positions with mortars.  The Brigades concluded by saying the attack lasted for several hours and that their fighters observed 'Israeli' helicopters landing at the site to evacuate the wounded. ğŸ”´ Stay updated with the latest global news: ğŸŒ Website: https://en.royanews.tv/ ğŸ“² Follow us for real-time news: ğŸ‘‰ Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/RoyaNewsEnglish ğŸ‘‰ Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/royanewsenglish ğŸ‘‰ Twitter: https://twitter.com/RoyaNewsEnglish  If you believe your copyright-protected work was posted on our YouTube channel without your authorization you may submit a copyright infringement notification at Youtube@roya.tv. title: Israel's Netanyahu Says Ready to Begin Ceasefire Negotiations to End Gaza War | N18G
description: Israel's Netanyahu Says Ready to Begin Ceasefire Negotiations to End Gaza War | N18G  Israel announced plans to resume Gaza truce negotiations, with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu issuing instructions to begin immediate talks for the release of all hostages and an end to the war on terms acceptable to Israel. title: Solidaritas Gaza, Warga Yaman Kecam Arab Saudi dan Mesir yang Diduga Dukung Israel
description: Download aplikasi berita TribunX di Play Store atau App Store untuk dapatkan pengalaman baru  TRIBUN-VIDEO.COM - Jutaan warga Yaman pada Jumat (22/8/2025) menggelar aksi solidaritas untuk Gaza di berbagai provinsi, menentang agresi Israel dan dukungan Amerika Serikat.  Mereka juga mengecam normalisasi hubungan sejumlah rezim Arab dengan Tel Aviv yang  terlibat dalam konspirasi melucuti kekuatan perlawanan.  Unjuk rasa ini mendukung operasi militer Yaman terhadap target Israel dan menyerukan eskalasi perlawanan.   (Almayadeen.net)  ---    Program: Tribun Video Update Host: Thalia Iza Editor: Reka Alfa  #solidaritasgaza #wargayaman #kecamsaudi #kecammesir #saudidukungisrael #mesirdukungisrael #konfliktimurTengah #perangisraelpalestina #solidaritaspalestina #dukunganYaman #beritatimurTengah #updateperanggaza

title: Pro-Palestinian protesters rally outside Israel Embassy in London over Gaza starvation
description: Pro-Palestinian protesters clanged pots and pans outside the Israeli Embassy in London on August 22, demonstrating against widespread hunger and starvation in Palestine's Gaza and the complicity of the UK government.
